    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_4]",
      "span_text": "Accumulating evidence suggests that RSV is a highly pleiotropic molecule that modulates abundant targets and thus influences numerous biochemical and molecular functions. Epidemiological studies indicate that the Mediterranean diet, which is rich in RSV, is associated with a reduced risk of carotid AS. Evidence from clinical trials indicated that RSV may protect against AS by improving gene expression in the vascular endothelium, and could be considered as a preventive agent. We previously found that RSV could penetrate into vascular endothelial cells and attenuate endothelial inflammation by inducing autophagy through the cyclic adenosine monophosphate (cAMP) signaling pathway. Nonetheless, little information is available regarding the effects of RSV on mtROS homeostasis regulation in endothelial cells."
    },
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_5]",
      "span_text": "Accumulating evidence suggests that RSV is a highly pleiotropic molecule that modulates abundant targets and thus influences numerous biochemical and molecular functions. Epidemiological studies indicate that the Mediterranean diet, which is rich in RSV, is associated with a reduced risk of carotid AS. Evidence from clinical trials indicated that RSV may protect against AS by improving gene expression in the vascular endothelium, and could be considered as a preventive agent. We previously found that RSV could penetrate into vascular endothelial cells and attenuate endothelial inflammation by inducing autophagy through the cyclic adenosine monophosphate (cAMP) signaling pathway. Nonetheless, little information is available regarding the effects of RSV on mtROS homeostasis regulation in endothelial cells."
